(72, 'import', 'AZ01', 'English Language and Literature', '039', 'English/Language Arts I (9th grade) - Part 2', 'English/Language Arts I (9th grade) courses build upon students’ prior knowledge of grammar, vocabulary, word usage, and the mechanics of writing and usually include the four aspects of language use: reading, writing, speaking, and listening. Typically, these courses introduce and define various genres of literature, with writing exercises often linked to reading selections.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '42207', NULL, '1', '01001', '01', 'English Language and Literature', '001', 'English/Language Arts I (9th grade)', 'English/Language Arts I (9th grade) courses build upon students’ prior knowledge of grammar, vocabulary, word usage, and the mechanics of writing and usually include the four aspects of language use: reading, writing, speaking, and listening. Typically, these courses introduce and define various genres of literature, with writing exercises often linked to reading selections.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:44:59', '2020-06-09 09:44:59'),
(73, 'import', 'AZ01', 'English Language and Literature', '045', 'English/Language Arts III (11th grade) - Part 2', 'English/Language Arts III (11th grade) courses continue to develop students’ writing skills, emphasizing clear, logical writing patterns, word choice, and usage, as students write essays and begin to learn the techniques of writing research papers. Students continue to read works of literature, which often form the backbone of the writing assignments. Literary conventions and stylistic devices may receive greater emphasis than in previous courses.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '42207', NULL, '1', '01003', '01', 'English Language and Literature', '003', 'English/Language Arts III (11th grade)', 'English/Language Arts III (11th grade) courses continue to develop students’ writing skills, emphasizing clear, logical writing patterns, word choice, and usage, as students write essays and begin to learn the techniques of writing research papers. Students continue to read works of literature, which often form the backbone of the writing assignments. Literary conventions and stylistic devices may receive greater emphasis than in previous courses.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:44:59', '2020-06-09 09:44:59'),
(74, 'import', 'AZ01', 'English Language and Literature', '033', 'Advanced ELA (9th grade) - Part 2', 'Any English/Language Arts (9th grade) course designed for students with advanced  knowledge of grammar, vocabulary, word usage, and the mechanics of writing and usually include the four aspects of language use: reading, writing, speaking, and listening. Typically, these courses introduce and define various genres of literature, with writing exercises often linked to reading selections.  *Aligns with 9th grade ELA standards in all strands.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '42207', NULL, '1', '01999', '01', 'English Language and Literature', '999', 'English Language and Literature—Other', 'Other English Language and Literature courses.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:44:59', '2020-06-09 09:44:59'),
(75, 'import', 'AZ01', 'English Language and Literature', '034', 'Advanced ELA (10th grade) - Part 2', 'Any English/Language Arts  (10th grade) courses for advanced students with a focus on composition and literature. Typically, students learn about the alternate aims and audiences of written compositions by writing persuasive, critical, and creative multi-paragraph essays and compositions. Through the study of various genres of literature, students can improve their reading rate and comprehension and develop the skills to determine the author’s intent and theme and to recognize the techniques used by the author to deliver his or her message.  *Aligns with 10th grade ELA standards in all strands.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '42207', NULL, '1', '01999', '01', 'English Language and Literature', '999', 'English Language and Literature—Other', 'Other English Language and Literature courses.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:44:59', '2020-06-09 09:44:59'),
(76, 'import', 'AZ01', 'English Language and Literature', '035', 'Advanced ELA (11th grade) - Part 2', 'Any English/Language Arts  (11th grade) courses designed to continue to develop advanced students’ writing skills, emphasizing clear, logical writing patterns, word choice, and usage, as students write essays and begin to learn the techniques of writing research papers. Students continue to read works of literature, which often form the backbone of the writing assignments. Literary conventions and stylistic devices may receive greater emphasis than in previous courses. *Aligns with 11th grade ELA standards in all strands.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '42207', NULL, '1', '01999', '01', 'English Language and Literature', '999', 'English Language and Literature—Other', 'Other English Language and Literature courses.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:44:59', '2020-06-09 09:44:59'),
