(81, 'import', 'AZ01', 'English Language and Literature', '002', 'English/Language Arts II (10th grade) -Part 1', 'This is the first part of  a two course cycle, credit will be granted after completion of the second part. (AZ01040)\nEnglish/Language Arts II (10th grade) courses usually offer a balanced focus on composition and literature. Typically, students learn about the alternate aims and audiences of written compositions by writing persuasive, critical, and creative multi-paragraph essays and compositions. Through the study of various genres of literature, students can improve their reading rate and comprehension and develop the skills to determine the author’s intent and theme and to recognize the techniques used by the author to deliver his or her message.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '42207', NULL, '2', '01002', '01', 'English Language and Literature', '002', 'English/Language Arts II (10th grade)', 'English/Language Arts II (10th grade) courses usually offer a balanced focus on composition and literature. Typically, students learn about the alternate aims and audiences of written compositions by writing persuasive, critical, and creative multi-paragraph essays and compositions. Through the study of various genres of literature, students can improve their reading rate and comprehension and develop the skills to determine the author’s intent and theme and to recognize the techniques used by the author to deliver his or her message.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:44:59', '2020-06-09 09:44:59'),
(82, 'import', 'AZ01', 'English Language and Literature', '003', 'English/Language Arts III (11th grade) -Part 1', 'This is the first part of  a two course cycle, credit will be granted after completion of the second part. (AZ01045)\nEnglish/Language Arts III (11th grade) courses continue to develop students’ writing skills, emphasizing clear, logical writing patterns, word choice, and usage, as students write essays and begin to learn the techniques of writing research papers. Students continue to read works of literature, which often form the backbone of the writing assignments. Literary conventions and stylistic devices may receive greater emphasis than in previous courses.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '42207', NULL, '2', '01003', '01', 'English Language and Literature', '003', 'English/Language Arts III (11th grade)', 'English/Language Arts III (11th grade) courses continue to develop students’ writing skills, emphasizing clear, logical writing patterns, word choice, and usage, as students write essays and begin to learn the techniques of writing research papers. Students continue to read works of literature, which often form the backbone of the writing assignments. Literary conventions and stylistic devices may receive greater emphasis than in previous courses.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:44:59', '2020-06-09 09:44:59');
