(527, 'import', 'AZ06', 'Foreign Language and Literature', '212', 'AP German Language and Culture', 'Designed by the College Board to parallel third-year college-level courses in German language, AP German Language and Culture courses build upon prior knowledge and develop students’ ability to express ideas, exchange opinions, and present information in German, both orally and in writing. These courses also help students understand and interpret written and spoken German. In addition, students explore the culture of German-speaking people in historical and contemporary contexts.\n', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '1', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '24264', '24', 'Foreign Language and Literature', '264', 'AP German Language and Culture \n', 'Designed by the College Board to parallel third-year college-level courses in German language, AP German Language and Culture courses build upon prior knowledge and develop students’ ability to express ideas, exchange opinions, and present information in German, both orally and in writing. These courses also help students understand and interpret written and spoken German. In addition, students explore the culture of German-speaking people in historical and contemporary contexts.\n', '0', '1', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:01', '2020-06-09 09:45:01'),
(528, 'import', 'AZ06', 'Foreign Language and Literature', '241', 'Germanic Language I', 'Designed to introduce students to a Germanic language not otherwise described (e.g., Dutch or Flemish) and culture, Germanic Language I courses emphasize basic grammar and syntax, simple vocabulary, and the spoken accent so that students can read, write, speak, and understand the language at a basic level within predictable areas of need, using customary courtesies and conventions.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '06241', '06', 'Foreign Language and Literature', '241', 'Germanic Language I', '--This course was archived at the National level -- Designed to introduce students to a Germanic language not otherwise described (e.g., Dutch or Flemish) and culture, Germanic Language I courses emphasize basic grammar and syntax, simple vocabulary, and the spoken accent so that students can read, write, speak, and understand the language at a basic level within predictable areas of need, using customary courtesies and conventions.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:01', '2020-06-09 09:45:01'),
(529, 'import', 'AZ06', 'Foreign Language and Literature', '242', 'Germanic Language II', 'Germanic Language II courses build upon skills developed in Germanic Language I, extending students’ ability to understand and express themselves in a Germanic language not otherwise described (e.g., Dutch or Flemish) and increasing their vocabulary. Typically, students learn how to engage in discourse for informative or social purposes, write expressions or passages that show understanding of sentence construction and the rules of grammar, and comprehend the language when spoken slowly. Students usually explore the customs, history, and art forms of appropriate people to deepen their understanding of the culture(s).', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '06242', '06', 'Foreign Language and Literature', '242', 'Germanic Language II', '--This course was archived at the National level -- Germanic Language II courses build upon skills developed in Germanic Language I, extending students’ ability to understand and express themselves in a Germanic language not otherwise described (e.g., Dutch or Flemish) and increasing their vocabulary. Typically, students learn how to engage in discourse for informative or social purposes, write expressions or passages that show understanding of sentence construction and the rules of grammar, and comprehend the language when spoken slowly. Students usually explore the customs, history, and art forms of appropriate people to deepen their understanding of the culture(s).', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:01', '2020-06-09 09:45:01'),
(530, 'import', 'AZ06', 'Foreign Language and Literature', '243', 'Germanic Language III', 'Germanic Language III courses focus on having students express increasingly complex concepts both verbally and in writing while showing some spontaneity. Comprehension goals for students may include attaining more facility and faster understanding when listening to the language spoken at normal rates, being able to paraphrase or summarize written passages, and conversing easily within limited situations.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '06243', '06', 'Foreign Language and Literature', '243', 'Germanic Language III', '--This course was archived at the National level -- Germanic Language III courses focus on having students express increasingly complex concepts both verbally and in writing while showing some spontaneity. Comprehension goals for students may include attaining more facility and faster understanding when listening to the language spoken at normal rates, being able to paraphrase or summarize written passages, and conversing easily within limited situations.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:01', '2020-06-09 09:45:01'),
(531, 'import', 'AZ06', 'Foreign Language and Literature', '244', 'Germanic Language IV', 'Germanic Language IV courses focus on advancing students’ skills and abilities to read, write, speak, and understand the Germanic Language being studied so that they can maintain simple conversations with sufficient vocabulary and an acceptable accent, have sufficient comprehension to understand speech spoken at a normal pace, read uncomplicated but authentic prose, and write narratives that indicate a good understanding of grammar and a strong vocabulary.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '06244', '06', 'Foreign Language and Literature', '244', 'Germanic Language IV', '--This course was archived at the National level -- Germanic Language IV courses focus on advancing students’ skills and abilities to read, write, speak, and understand the Germanic Language being studied so that they can maintain simple conversations with sufficient vocabulary and an acceptable accent, have sufficient comprehension to understand speech spoken at a normal pace, read uncomplicated but authentic prose, and write narratives that indicate a good understanding of grammar and a strong vocabulary.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:01', '2020-06-09 09:45:01'),
(532, 'import', 'AZ06', 'Foreign Language and Literature', '245', 'Germanic Language V', 'Germanic Language V courses extend students’ facility with the language so that they are able to understand, initiate, and sustain general conversations on topics beyond basic survival needs. Reading and writing tasks will usually include all normal verb tenses (present, past, and future).', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '06245', '06', 'Foreign Language and Literature', '245', 'Germanic Language V', '--This course was archived at the National level -- Germanic Language V courses extend students’ facility with the language so that they are able to understand, initiate, and sustain general conversations on topics beyond basic survival needs. Reading and writing tasks will usually include all normal verb tenses (present, past, and future).', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:01', '2020-06-09 09:45:01');
