(780, 'import', 'AZ06', 'Foreign Language and Literature', '851', 'IB Language B—Indic Language', 'IB Language B—Indic Language courses prepare students to take the International Baccalaureate Language B exams at either the Subsidiary or Higher level. These courses focus on improving students’ accuracy and fluency in oral and written communication (usually in the students’ “second” language). Students preparing to take the Subsidiary level exam will be able to understand native speakers; students preparing for the Higher level exam will be able to communicate fluently at native speed.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '1', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '06851', '06', 'Foreign Language and Literature', '851', 'IB Language B—Indic Language', '--This course was archived at the National level -- IB Language B—Indic Language courses prepare students to take the International Baccalaureate Language B exams at either the standard or higher level. These courses focus on improving students’ accuracy and fluency in oral and written communication (usually in the students’ “second” language). Students preparing to take the standard level exam will be able to understand native speakers; students preparing for the higher level exam will be able to communicate fluently at native speed.', '1', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:02', '2020-06-09 09:45:02'),
