(1013, 'import', 'AZ10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '997', 'Computer and Information Sciences—Independent Study', 'Computer and Information Sciences—Independent Study courses, often conducted with instructors as mentors, enable students to explore computer-related topics of interest. Independent Study courses may serve as an opportunity for students to expand their expertise in a particular specialization, to explore a topic in greater detail, or to develop more advanced skills.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '10997', '10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '997', 'Computer and Information Sciences—Independent Study', 'Computer and Information Sciences—Independent Study courses, often conducted with instructors as mentors, enable students to explore computer-related topics of interest. Independent Study courses may serve as an opportunity for students to expand their expertise in a particular specialization, to explore a topic in greater detail, or to develop more advanced skills.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:02', '2020-06-09 09:45:02'),
(1014, 'import', 'AZ10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '998', 'Computer and Information Sciences—Workplace Experience', 'Computer and Information Sciences—Workplace Experience courses provide students with work experience in fields related to computer and/or information sciences. Goals are typically set cooperatively by the student, teacher, and employer (although students are not necessarily paid). These courses may include classroom activities as well, involving further study of the field or discussion regarding experiences that students encounter in the workplace.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '10998', '10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '998', 'Computer and Information Sciences—Workplace Experience', 'Computer and Information Sciences—Workplace Experience courses provide students with work experience in fields related to computer and/or information sciences. Goals are typically set cooperatively by the student, teacher, and employer (although students are not necessarily paid). These courses may include classroom activities as well, involving further study of the field or discussion regarding experiences that students encounter in the workplace.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:02', '2020-06-09 09:45:02'),
(1015, 'import', 'AZ10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '999', 'Computer and Information Sciences—Other', 'Other Computer and Information Sciences courses.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '10999', '10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '999', 'Computer and Information Sciences—Other', 'Other Computer and Information Sciences courses.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:02', '2020-06-09 09:45:02'),
(1016, 'import', 'AZ10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '181', 'Cambridge AS Level Computing', 'The aim of the A and AS Level Computing syllabus is to develop an understanding of how computers are used to solve a wide range of problems. Students learn about a variety of different computers, and also look at the ways in which computers are organized in terms of software, data, hardware, communications and people. Students develop the skills necessary to apply their understanding to the development of computer-based solutions. As they progress, students learn about the main principles of systems analysis and design, looking at different methods of problem formulation, and the planning of solutions. They also consider systematic methods of solution implementation, testing and documentation.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '41030', NULL, '1', '10199', '10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '199', 'Computer Programming—Other', 'Other Computer Programming courses.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:02', '2020-06-09 09:45:02'),
(1017, 'import', 'AZ10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '161', 'Computer Science Principles', 'Computer Science Principles courses provide students the opportunity use programming, computational thinking, and data analytics to create digital artifacts and documents representing design and analysis in areas including the Internet, algorithms, and the impact that these have on science, business, and society. Computer Science Principles courses teach students to use computational tools and techniques including abstraction, modeling, and simulation to collaborate in solving problems that connect computation to their lives.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '41699', NULL, '1', '10011', '10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '011', 'Computer Science Principles', 'Computer Science Principles courses provide students the opportunity use programming, computational thinking, and data analytics to create digital artifacts and documents representing design and analysis in areas including the Internet, algorithms, and the impact that these have on science, business, and society. Computer Science Principles courses teach students to use computational tools and techniques including abstraction, modeling, and simulation to collaborate in solving problems that connect computation to their lives.', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:02', '2020-06-09 09:45:02'),
(1018, 'import', 'AZ10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '162', 'Exploring Computer Science', 'Exploring Computer Science courses present students with the conceptual underpinnings of computer science through an exploration of human computer interaction, web design, computer programming, data modeling, and robotics.  While these courses include programming, the focus is on the computational practices associated with doing computer science, rather than just a narrow focus on coding, syntax, or tools.  Exploring Computer Science courses teach students the computational practices of algorithm design, problem solving, and programming within a context that is relevant to their lives.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '41699', NULL, '1', '10012', '10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '012', 'Exploring Computer Science', 'Exploring Computer Science courses present students with the conceptual underpinnings of computer science through an exploration of human computer interaction, web design, computer programming, data modeling, and robotics.  While these courses include programming, the focus is on the computational practices associated with doing computer science, rather than just a narrow focus on coding, syntax, or tools.  Exploring Computer Science courses teach students the computational practices of algorithm design, problem solving, and programming within a context that is relevant to their lives.', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:02', '2020-06-09 09:45:02'),
(1019, 'import', 'AZ10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '205', 'Computer Gaming and Design', 'Computer Gaming and Design courses prepare students to design computer games by studying design, animation, artistic concepts, digital imaging, coding, scripting, multimedia production, and game play strategies. Advanced course topics include, but are not limited to, level design, environment and 3D modeling, scene and set design, motion capture, and texture mapping.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '41699', NULL, '1', '10205', '10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '205', 'Computer Gaming and Design', 'Computer Gaming and Design courses prepare students to design computer games by studying design, animation, artistic concepts, digital imaging, coding, scripting, multimedia production, and game play strategies. Advanced course topics include, but are not limited to, level design, environment and 3D modeling, scene and set design, motion capture, and texture mapping.', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:02', '2020-06-09 09:45:02'),
(1020, 'import', 'AZ10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '206', 'Mobile Applications', 'Mobile Applications courses provide students with opportunities to create applications for mobile devices using a variety of commercial and open source software. These courses typically address the installation and modification of these applications, as well as customer service skills to handle user issues.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '41699', NULL, '1', '10206', '10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '206', 'Mobile Applications', 'Mobile Applications courses provide students with opportunities to create applications for mobile devices using a variety of commercial and open source software. These courses typically address the installation and modification of these applications, as well as customer service skills to handle user issues.', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:02', '2020-06-09 09:45:02'),
(1021, 'import', 'AZ10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '207', 'Computer Forensics', 'Computer Forensics courses address the preservation, identification, extraction, documentation, and interpretation of computer data. Topics covered may include legal concepts, evidence handling and preservation, file system structures, chain of custody, and identification and recovery of computer data. These courses may also cover the need to perform an investigation and how to collect evidence and analyze data.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '41699', NULL, '1', '10301', '10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '301', 'Computer Forensics', 'Computer Forensics courses address the preservation, identification, extraction, documentation, and interpretation of computer data. Topics covered may include legal concepts, evidence handling and preservation, file system structures, chain of custody, and identification and recovery of computer data. These courses may also cover the need to perform an investigation and how to collect evidence and analyze data.', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:02', '2020-06-09 09:45:02'),
(1022, 'import', 'AZ10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '208', 'Cyber Crime', 'Cyber Crime courses cover legal and ethical behavior associated with network security. Topics may include discussions about current common practices used to secure networks, how to test these networks, and presents methods that can be used to create a secure network environment. These courses may also cover the impact federal and state legislation has had on information technology practices.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '41699', NULL, '1', '10302', '10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '302', 'Cyber Crime', 'Cyber Crime courses cover legal and ethical behavior associated with network security. Topics may include discussions about current common practices used to secure networks, how to test these networks, and presents methods that can be used to create a secure network environment. These courses may also cover the impact federal and state legislation has had on information technology practices.', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1023, 'import', 'AZ10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '112', 'Local Area Networking', 'Local Area Networking courses introduce students to local area networking (LAN) administration skills, operating systems, basic user skills, defining network objects, building a simple LAN topology applying principles of cabling, LAN switching, designing file systems, managing user access, securing file systems, working with directory service software security, implementing network printing, implementing login scripts, and managing user environments.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '41699', NULL, '1', '10112', '10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '112', 'Local Area Networking', 'Local Area Networking courses introduce students to local area networking (LAN) administration skills, operating systems, basic user skills, defining network objects, building a simple LAN topology applying principles of cabling, LAN switching, designing file systems, managing user access, securing file systems, working with directory service software security, implementing network printing, implementing login scripts, and managing user environments.', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1024, 'import', 'AZ10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '009', 'Internet Skills', 'Internet Skills courses introduce students to the World Wide Web and the Internet. Course content may include search techniques and algorithms, web browser utilization, website creation, and the history of the Internet.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '42207', NULL, '1', '10009', '10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '009', 'Internet Skills', 'Internet Skills courses introduce students to the World Wide Web and the Internet. Course content may include search techniques and algorithms, web browser utilization, website creation, and the history of the Internet.', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1025, 'import', 'AZ10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '013', 'PLTW Introduction to Computer Science', 'Following Project Lead the Way’s suggested curriculum, PLTW Introduction to Computer Science courses prepare students for other computer science courses and introduce them to the impact and application of computing. These courses provide students with the opportunity to create interactive stories, develop simple mobile applications, and analyze personal health and social habit data using spreadsheet programs.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '42207', NULL, '1', '10013', '10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '013', 'PLTW Computer Science Essentials', 'Following Project Lead the Way’s suggested curriculum, PLTW Computer Science Essentials (formerly known as PLTW Introduction to Computer Science) courses introduce students to computational thinking concepts, fundamentals, and tools. Students will increase their understanding of programming languages through the use of visual and text-based programming. Projects will include the creation of apps and websites to address real-life topics and problems.', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1026, 'import', 'AZ10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '014', 'PLTW Computer Science Applications', 'Following Project Lead the Way’s suggested curriculum to prepare students for the College Board’s Advanced Placement Computer Science A exam, PLTW Computer Science Applications courses focus on integrating technologies across multiple platforms and networks. In these courses, students collaborate to produce programs and analyze, adapt, and improve each other’s programs using industry-standard programming and software tools.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '42207', NULL, '1', '10014', '10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '014', 'PLTW Computer Science A', 'Following Project Lead the Way’s suggested curriculum to prepare students for the College Board’s Advanced Placement Computer Science A exam, PLTW Computer Science A (formerly known as PLTW Computer Science Applications) courses focus on extending students\' computational thinking skills through the use of various industry-standard programming and software tools. In these courses, students collaborate to design and produce solutions to real-life problems.', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1027, 'import', 'AZ10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '010', 'Introduction to Computer Information Systems', 'CTE CIP Code: 43.0116.10 Includes description of computer hardware and software, computer terminology, the data processing cycle, and characteristics of programming languages, with emphasis on the use of applications software in processing business data.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, '42901', NULL, '1', '10003', '10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '003', 'Computer and Information Technology', 'Computer and Information Technology courses teach students to operate and use computer and information technology, emphasizing their role as tools to communicate more effectively, conduct research more efficiently, and increase productivity. Course content includes the legal and ethical issues involved with computer technology and use.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1028, 'import', 'AZ10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '164', 'Computer Programming Logic', 'CTE CIP Code: 11.9999.40 This course is an introduction to the fundamental techniques used in designing computer programs.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, '42901', NULL, '1', '10152', '10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '152', 'Computer Programming', 'Computer Programming courses provide students with the knowledge and skills necessary to construct computer programs in one or more languages. Computer coding and program structure are often introduced with the BASIC language, but other computer languages, such as Visual Basic (VB), Java, Pascal, C++, and COBOL, may be used instead. Initially, students learn to structure, create, document, and debug computer programs, and as they progress, more emphasis is placed on design, style, clarity, and efficiency. Students may apply the skills they learn to relevant applications such as modeling, data management, graphics, and text-processing.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1029, 'import', 'AZ10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '165', 'Computer Programming: Visual BASIC', 'CTE CIP Code: 11.9999.45 Computer programming as a problem-solving technique, regardless of the student’s area of study. The BASIC language is used to write, debug, and document business application programs to demonstrate proficiency in using BASIC.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, '42901', NULL, '1', '10156', '10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '156', 'Computer Programming—Other Language', 'Computer Programming—Other Language courses provide students with the opportunity to gain expertise in computer programs using languages other than those specified (such as Pascal, FORTRAN, or emerging languages). As with other computer programming courses, the emphasis is on how to structure and document computer programs, using problem-solving techniques. As students advance, they learn to capitalize on the features and strengths of the language being used.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1030, 'import', 'AZ10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '166', 'Computer Programming: C Sharp', 'CTE CIP Code: 11.9999.50 Fundamental techniques using the C# (C Sharp) language.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, '42901', NULL, '1', '10156', '10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '156', 'Computer Programming—Other Language', 'Computer Programming—Other Language courses provide students with the opportunity to gain expertise in computer programs using languages other than those specified (such as Pascal, FORTRAN, or emerging languages). As with other computer programming courses, the emphasis is on how to structure and document computer programs, using problem-solving techniques. As students advance, they learn to capitalize on the features and strengths of the language being used.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1031, 'import', 'AZ10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '167', 'Introduction to Operating Systems', 'CTE CIP Code: 11.9999.55 The internal logic of various parts of common operating systems and access to Windows, DOS, and UNIX/Linux Systems.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, '42901', NULL, '1', '10999', '10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '999', 'Computer and Information Sciences—Other', 'Other Computer and Information Sciences courses.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1032, 'import', 'AZ10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '168', 'Structured Systems Analysis and Design', 'CTE CIP Code: 11.9999.60 An introduction to the fundamental tools and techniques used in analyzing organizational information systems. Topics include systems research, design, revision, and implementation of information systems. Students complete one or more projects as members of systems teams.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, '42901', NULL, '1', '10999', '10', 'Computer and Information Sciences', '999', 'Computer and Information Sciences—Other', 'Other Computer and Information Sciences courses.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1033, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '001', 'Introduction to Communication', 'Introduction to Communication courses enable students to understand and critically evaluate the role of media in society. Course content typically includes investigation of visual images, printed material, and audio segments as tools of information, entertainment, and propaganda; improvement of presentation and evaluative skills in relation to mass media; recognition of various techniques for delivery of a particular message; and, in some cases, creation of a media product. The course may concentrate on a particular medium.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11001', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '001', 'Introduction to Communication', 'Introduction to Communication courses enable students to understand and critically evaluate the role of media in society. Course content typically includes investigation of visual images, printed material, and audio segments as tools of information, entertainment, and propaganda; improvement of presentation and evaluative skills in relation to mass media; recognition of various techniques for delivery of a particular message; and, in some cases, creation of a media product. The course may concentrate on a particular medium.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1034, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '002', 'Communication Technology', 'Communication Technology courses enable students to effectively communicate ideas and information through experiences dealing with drafting, design, electronic communication, graphic arts, printing process, photography, telecommunications, and computers. Additional topics covered in the course include information storage and retrieval. Drafting equipment may be used to make scale drawings, including multi-view drawing, photographs, and poster mock-ups.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11002', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '002', 'Communication Technology', 'Communication Technology courses enable students to effectively communicate ideas and information through experiences dealing with drafting, design, electronic communication, graphic arts, printing process, photography, telecommunications, and computers. Additional topics covered in the course include information storage and retrieval. Drafting equipment may be used to make scale drawings, including multi-view drawing, photographs, and poster mock-ups.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1035, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '003', 'Film & TV II', 'CTE CIP Code:  10.0200.95\nThis course will be the development of a portfolio with the following projects: Classroom, School, Community related to Film & TV.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11003', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '003', 'Particular Topics in Communication', 'These courses examine specific topics in communication other than those already described elsewhere in this classification system.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1036, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '047', 'Communication—Independent Study', 'Communication—Independent Study courses, often conducted with instructors as mentors, enable students to explore topics of interest related to mass communications. Independent Study courses may serve as an opportunity for students to expand their expertise in a particular application, to explore a topic in greater detail, or to develop more advanced skills.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11047', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '047', 'Communication—Independent Study', 'Communication—Independent Study courses, often conducted with instructors as mentors, enable students to explore topics of interest related to mass communications. Independent Study courses may serve as an opportunity for students to expand their expertise in a particular application, to explore a topic in greater detail, or to develop more advanced skills.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1037, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '048', 'Communications Media Technologies- Cooperative Education', 'CTE CIP Code:  10.0200.80\nThis course utilizes a cooperative education methodology to combine school-based and supervised work-based learning experiences directly related to the standards identified for the designated Communications Media Technologies program.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11048', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '048', 'Communication—Workplace Experience', 'Communication—Workplace Experience courses provide students with work experience in a field related to communication. Goals are typically set cooperatively by the student, teacher, and employer (although students are not necessarily paid). These courses may include classroom activities as well, involving further study of the field or discussion regarding experiences that students encounter in the workplace.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1038, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '049', 'Communications Media Technologies- Internship', 'CTE CIP Code:  10.0200.75\nThis course provides students an opportunity to apply previously developed knowledge and skills into a structured work experience within the specific option they have studied.  This work experience may or may not require classroom instruction, may be paid or unpaid, and is available for 12th graders who have completed at least one Carnegie unit of study in the designated Communications Media Technologies program.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11049', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '049', 'Communication—Other', 'Other Communication courses.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1039, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '051', 'Audio/Visual Production', 'Audio/Visual Production courses provide students with the knowledge and skills necessary for television, video, film, and/or radio production. Writing scripts, camera operation, use of graphics and other visuals, lighting, audio techniques, editing, production principles, and career opportunities are typical topics covered within production courses. Students are usually required to produce their own program or segment. Additional topics such as broadcast industry regulations, radio/TV operation, power of the medium, photography, transmission technology, and so on may be included.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11051', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '051', 'Audio/Visual Production', 'Audio/Visual Production courses provide students with the knowledge and skills necessary for television, video, film, and/or radio production. Writing scripts, camera operation, use of graphics and other visuals, lighting, audio techniques, editing, production principles, and career opportunities are typical topics covered within production courses. Students are usually required to produce their own program or segment. Additional topics such as broadcast industry regulations, radio/TV operation, power of the medium, photography, transmission technology, and so on may be included.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1040, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '052', 'Commercial Photography', 'Commercial Photography courses provide instruction in the use of cameras and laboratory filmprocessing techniques. Topics covered in the course include composition and color dynamics; contact printing; enlarging; developing film; use of camera meters, air brushes, and other photographic equipment; portrait, commercial, and industrial photography; processing microfilm; and preparing copy for printing or for graphic-arts processing.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11052', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '052', 'Commercial Photography', 'Commercial Photography courses provide instruction in the use of cameras and laboratory filmprocessing techniques. Topics covered in the course include composition and color dynamics; contact printing; enlarging; developing film; use of camera meters, air brushes, and other photographic equipment; portrait, commercial, and industrial photography; processing microfilm; and preparing copy for printing or for graphic-arts processing.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1041, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '053', 'Photographic Laboratory and Darkroom', 'Photographic Laboratory and Darkroom courses prepare students to develop and print still or motion picture film. Topics covered in the course may include controlling resultant prints; touching up negatives; and finishing, coloring, restoring, and copying prints.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11053', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '053', 'Photographic Laboratory and Darkroom', 'Photographic Laboratory and Darkroom courses prepare students to develop and print still or motion picture film. Topics covered in the course may include controlling resultant prints; touching up negatives; and finishing, coloring, restoring, and copying prints.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1042, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '054', 'Photo Imaging', 'Photo Imaging courses provide students with the opportunity to effectively communicate ideas and information via digital, film, still and video photography. Topics covered typically include composition, layout, lighting and supplies. More advanced courses may include instruction in specialized camera and equipment maintenance, application to commercial and industrial need and photography business operations.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11054', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '054', 'Photo Imaging', 'Photo Imaging courses provide students with the opportunity to effectively communicate ideas and information via digital, film, still and video photography. Topics covered typically include composition, layout, lighting and supplies. More advanced courses may include instruction in specialized camera and equipment maintenance, application to commercial and industrial need and photography business operations.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1043, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '055', 'Video', 'Video courses enable students to explore video communications, incorporating both the technical and artistic aspects of video media. Topics covered in the course include the use of video equipment and techniques, and students typically create a video presentation. Advanced course topics may include creating various forms of film media including silent film; sport and music video; and self portrait video.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11055', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '055', 'Video', 'Video courses enable students to explore video communications, incorporating both the technical and artistic aspects of video media. Topics covered in the course include the use of video equipment and techniques, and students typically create a video presentation. Advanced course topics may include creating various forms of film media including silent film; sport and music video; and self portrait video.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1044, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '056', 'Music/Audio Production I', 'CTE CIP Code:  10.0200.00\nThis course will prepare the student to integrate pre-production, production, post-production, Deliver/Distribute, Quality Assurance, and Presentation phases of Music & Audio Productions.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11056', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '056', 'Particular Topics in Audio/Video Technology and Film', 'These courses examine specific topics in audio and video technology and film other than those already described elsewhere in this classification system.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1045, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '097', 'Music/Audio Production II', 'CTE CIP Code:  10.0200.05\nThis course will be the development of a portfolio with the following projects: Classroom, School, Community related to Music/Audio Production.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11097', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '097', 'Audio/Video Technology and Film—Independent Study', 'Audio/Video Technology and Film—Independent Study courses, often conducted with instructors as mentors, enable students to explore topics of interest related to A/V technology or film. Independent Study courses may serve as an opportunity for students to expand their expertise in a particular application, to explore a topic in greater detail, or to develop more advanced skills.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1046, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '098', 'Graphic Communications - Cooperative Education', 'CTE CIP Code:  10.0300.80\nThis course utilizes a cooperative education methodology to combine school-based and supervised work-based learning experiences directly related to the standards identified for the Graphic Communications program.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11098', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '098', 'Audio/Video Technology and Film—Workplace Experience', 'Audio/Video Technology and Film—Workplace Experience courses provide students with work experience in a field related to audio/visual technology and/or film. Goals are typically set cooperatively by the student, teacher, and employer (although students are not necessarily paid). These courses may include classroom activities as well, involving further study of the field or discussion regarding experiences that students encounter in the workplace.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1047, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '099', 'Graphic Communications - Internship', 'CTE CIP Code:  10.0300.75\nThis course provides CTE students an opportunity to engage in learning through participation in a structured work experience that can be either paid or unpaid and does not necessarily require classroom instruction that involves the application of previously developed Graphic Communications knowledge and skills.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11099', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '099', 'Audio/Video Technology and Film—Other', 'Other Audio/Video Technology and Film courses.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1048, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '101', 'Journalism I', 'CTE CIP Code:  10.0200.40\nThis course will prepare the student to integrate pre-production, production, post-production, Deliver/Distribute, Quality Assurance, and Presentation phases of Journalism.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11101', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '101', 'Journalism', 'Journalism courses (typically associated with the production of a school newspaper, yearbook, or literary magazine) emphasize writing style and technique as well as production values and organization. Journalism courses introduce students to the concepts of newsworthiness and press responsibility; develop students’ skills in writing and editing stories, headlines, and captions; and teach students the principles of production design, layout, and printing. Photography and photojournalism skills may be included.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1049, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '102', 'Journalism II', 'CTE CIP Code:  10.0200.45\nThis course will be the development of a portfolio with the following projects: Classroom, School, Community related to Journalism.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11102', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '102', 'Photojournalism', 'Photojournalism courses expose students to the manner in which photography is used to convey information and experiences. Typically coordinated with production of the school newspaper, yearbook, or other media product, photojournalism courses provide students with the opportunity to improve their photo composition and film development skills, and to apply their art to journalistic endeavors.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1050, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '103', 'Broadcasting Technology', 'Broadcasting Technology courses provide students with the knowledge and skills to produce television broadcast programs. Typically, students prepare and produce short programs, learning the technical aspects of the operation and how to evaluate programming and assess audience reaction and impact.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11103', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '103', 'Broadcasting Technology', 'Broadcasting Technology courses provide students with the knowledge and skills to produce television broadcast programs. Typically, students prepare and produce short programs, learning the technical aspects of the operation and how to evaluate programming and assess audience reaction and impact.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1051, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '104', 'Publication Production', 'Publication Production courses provide students with the knowledge and skills necessary to produce the school newspaper, yearbook, literary magazine, or other printed publication. Students may gain experience in several components (writing, editing, layout, production, and so on) or may focus on a single aspect while producing the publication.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11104', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '104', 'Publication Production', 'Publication Production courses provide students with the knowledge and skills necessary to produce the school newspaper, yearbook, literary magazine, or other printed publication. Students may gain experience in several components (writing, editing, layout, production, and so on) or may focus on a single aspect while producing the publication.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1052, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '105', 'Particular Topics in Journalism and Broadcasting', 'These courses examine specific topics in journalism and broadcasting other than those already described.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11105', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '105', 'Particular Topics in Journalism and Broadcasting', 'These courses examine specific topics in journalism and broadcasting other than those already described elsewhere in this classification system.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1053, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '147', 'Journalism and Broadcasting—Independent Study', 'Journalism and Broadcasting—Independent Study courses, often conducted with instructors as mentors, enable students to explore topics of interest related to journalism, broadcasting, and mass media. Independent Study courses may serve as an opportunity for students to expand their expertise in a particular application, to explore a topic in greater detail, or to develop more advanced skills.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11147', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '147', 'Journalism and Broadcasting—Independent Study', 'Journalism and Broadcasting—Independent Study courses, often conducted with instructors as mentors, enable students to explore topics of interest related to journalism, broadcasting, and mass media. Independent Study courses may serve as an opportunity for students to expand their expertise in a particular application, to explore a topic in greater detail, or to develop more advanced skills.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
(1054, 'import', 'AZ11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '148', 'Journalism and Broadcasting—Workplace Experience', 'Journalism and Broadcasting—Workplace Experience courses provide students with work experience in a field related to journalism or broadcasting. Goals are typically set cooperatively by the student, teacher, and employer (although students are not necessarily paid). These courses may include classroom activities as well, involving further study of the field or discussion regarding experiences that students encounter in the workplace.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '11148', '11', 'Communications and Audio/Visual Tech', '148', 'Journalism and Broadcasting—Workplace Experience', 'Journalism and Broadcasting—Workplace Experience courses provide students with work experience in a field related to journalism or broadcasting. Goals are typically set cooperatively by the student, teacher, and employer (although students are not necessarily paid). These courses may include classroom activities as well, involving further study of the field or discussion regarding experiences that students encounter in the workplace.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:03', '2020-06-09 09:45:03'),
