(1422, 'import', 'AZ17', 'Architecture and Construction', '009', 'Building Maintenance I', 'CTE CIP Code: 46.0401.10 Building Maintenance courses train students to maintain commercial, industrial, and residential buildings and homes. Instruction is provided in the basic maintenance and repair of air conditioning, heating, plumbing, electrical, and other mechanical systems. Topics covered may include identifying and using hand and power tools safely; installing and repairing floor coverings, walls, and ceilings; installing and repairing doors, windows, screens, and cabinets; applying finishes to prepared surfaces; and repairing roofs, masonry, plumbing, and electrical systems.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '42551', NULL, '1', '17009', '17', 'Architecture and Construction', '009', 'Building Maintenance', 'Building Maintenance courses train students to maintain commercial, industrial, and residential buildings and homes. Instruction is provided in the basic maintenance and repair of air conditioning, heating, plumbing, electrical, and other mechanical systems. Topics covered may include identifying and using hand and power tools safely; installing and repairing floor coverings, walls, and ceilings; installing and repairing doors, windows, screens, and cabinets; applying finishes to prepared surfaces; and repairing roofs, masonry, plumbing, and electrical systems.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:04', '2020-06-09 09:45:04'),
