(1471, 'import', 'AZ18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '248', 'Agricultural Business Management - Agriscience - Cooperative Education', 'CTE CIP Code:  01.0100.80\nThis course utilizes a cooperative education methodology to combine school-based and supervised work-based learning experiences directly related to the standards identified for the Agricultural Business Management - Agriscience program.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', '44012', '1', '18248', '18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '248', 'Agribusiness—Workplace Experience', 'Agribusiness—Workplace Experience courses provide work experience in fields related to agribusiness. Goals are typically set cooperatively by the student, teacher, and employer (although students are not necessarily paid). These courses may include classroom activities as well, involving further study of the field or discussion regarding experiences that students encounter in the workplace.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:04', '2020-06-09 09:45:04'),
(1472, 'import', 'AZ18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '249', 'Agricultural Business Management - Agriscience - Internship', 'CTE CIP Code:  01.0100.75\nThis course provides students an opportunity to apply previously developed knowledge and skill in Agricultural Business Management - Agriscience into a structured work experience within the same field of study. This work experience doesn\'t necessarily require classroom instruction and may be paid or unpaid. This is part of the student’s SAE component.', 'The Environmental Service Systems program is being discontinued. No new Environmental Service Systems programs may be added for the 2018-2019 school year. The final year a district may offer an Environmental Service Systems program will be the 2019-2020 school year. The Environmental Service Systems program has been determined to not be eligible for JTED funding. The program will continue to be \neligible for CTE Federal Perkins and CTE State Priority funding for the 2018-2019 and 2019-2020 school years. This course will archive 06/30/2020.', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', '44012', '1', '18249', '18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '249', 'Agribusiness—Other', 'Other Agribusiness Courses', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:04', '2020-06-09 09:45:04'),
(1473, 'import', 'AZ18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '301', 'Agricultural Production', 'Agricultural Production courses combine content related to animal and plant production, providing comprehensive coverage of the production functions of the agricultural industry. These courses typically cover such topics as care and management of farm animals, crop production and harvesting, plant and animal insect and disease control, efficient resource management, and farm management.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '18301', '18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '301', 'Agricultural Production', 'Agricultural Production courses combine content related to animal and plant production, providing comprehensive coverage of the production functions of the agricultural industry. These courses typically cover such topics as care and management of farm animals, crop production and harvesting, plant and animal insect and disease control, efficient resource management, and farm management.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:04', '2020-06-09 09:45:04'),
(1474, 'import', 'AZ18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '302', 'Agricultural Processing', 'Agricultural Processing courses impart the knowledge and skills needed to bring animal and plant products to market. They may cover a wide variety of topics, including care and maintenance of animals or plants, quality selection and preservation, equipment care and sanitation, government regulations, and marketing and consumer trends. Agricultural Processing courses may present an overview of agricultural processing or may specialize in particular types of products.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '18302', '18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '302', 'Agricultural Processing', 'Agricultural Processing courses impart the knowledge and skills needed to bring animal and plant products to market. They may cover a wide variety of topics, including care and maintenance of animals or plants, quality selection and preservation, equipment care and sanitation, government regulations, and marketing and consumer trends. Agricultural Processing courses may present an overview of agricultural processing or may specialize in particular types of products.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:04', '2020-06-09 09:45:04'),
(1475, 'import', 'AZ18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '303', 'Plant Processing', 'Plant Processing courses impart the knowledge and skills needed to bring plant products to market. They may cover a wide variety of topics, including plant production, quality selection and preservation, equipment care and sanitation, government regulations, and marketing and consumer trends. Plant Processing courses may present an overview of product processing or may specialize in specific plant products.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '18303', '18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '303', 'Plant Processing', 'Plant Processing courses impart the knowledge and skills needed to bring plant products to market. They may cover a wide variety of topics, including plant production, quality selection and preservation, equipment care and sanitation, government regulations, and marketing and consumer trends. Plant Processing courses may present an overview of product processing or may specialize in specific plant products.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:04', '2020-06-09 09:45:04'),
(1476, 'import', 'AZ18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '304', 'Animal Processing', 'Animal Processing courses impart the knowledge and skills needed to bring animal products to market. Although these courses may present an overview of animal care and maintenance, they typically emphasize quality selection, product preservation, equipment care and sanitation, government regulations, and marketing and consumer trends. Animal Processing courses may present an overview of several types of animal products or may specialize in particular products, such as meat, leather, wool, dairy products, and so on.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '18304', '18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '304', 'Animal Processing', 'Animal Processing courses impart the knowledge and skills needed to bring animal products to market. Although these courses may present an overview of animal care and maintenance, they typically emphasize quality selection, product preservation, equipment care and sanitation, government regulations, and marketing and consumer trends. Animal Processing courses may present an overview of several types of animal products or may specialize in particular products, such as meat, leather, wool, dairy products, and so on.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:04', '2020-06-09 09:45:04'),
(1477, 'import', 'AZ18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '305', 'Food Products and Processing Systems', 'CTE CIP Code:  01.0100.20\nPrepares students for careers in food processing and preserving, packaging, distribution, government monitoring & regulation.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '18305', '18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '305', 'Food Product Processing', 'Food Product Processing courses impart the knowledge and skills needed to produce and manufacture food products for the consumer market. These courses focus on food products while covering a variety of topics, such as quality selection and preservation, equipment care and sanitation, government regulations, marketing, consumer trends, and product research and development.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:04', '2020-06-09 09:45:04'),
(1478, 'import', 'AZ18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '306', 'Aquaculture', 'Aquaculture courses impart the knowledge and skills needed for producing fish, plants, and other species living in an aquatic environment, and course topics typically include the selection, propagation, harvesting, and marketing of those species. Instruction may also address aquatic and marine biology, ecosystems, water quality and management, and business practices.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '18306', '18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '306', 'Aquaculture', 'Aquaculture courses impart the knowledge and skills needed for producing fish, plants, and other species living in an aquatic environment, and course topics typically include the selection, propagation, harvesting, and marketing of those species. Instruction may also address aquatic and marine biology, ecosystems, water quality and management, and business practices.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:04', '2020-06-09 09:45:04'),
(1479, 'import', 'AZ18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '307', 'Agriculture and Society', 'Agriculture and Society courses provide an overview of the importance of, impact on, and relationships between agricultural endeavors and society at large. These courses typically emphasize economic and environmental factors and impacts (such as urban and agricultural water use) and the influences of society on agricultural endeavors (including production, processing, and distribution). Current technological advances (such as genetic engineering) may also be discussed.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '18307', '18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '307', 'Agriculture and Society', 'Agriculture and Society courses provide an overview of the importance of, impact on, and relationships between agricultural endeavors and society at large. These courses typically emphasize economic and environmental factors and impacts (such as urban and agricultural water use) and the influences of society on agricultural endeavors (including production, processing, and distribution). Current technological advances (such as genetic engineering) may also be discussed.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:04', '2020-06-09 09:45:04'),
(1480, 'import', 'AZ18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '308', 'Agricultural Business Management - Agriscience', 'CTE CIP Code:  01.0100.14\nThese Standards are designed to deliver the lab science standards associated with the Agriculture, Food and Natural Resources career cluster. Lab science credit for college entrance and secondary graduation is available if these standards are met and a Program Review has been completed. It is recommended that these standards be covered in course sequences during the 10th through 12th grades. This specific course is the 11th grade course.', '', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '18308', '18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '308', 'Agricultural Biotechnology', 'Agricultural Biotechnology courses apply biological principles and understanding to plant and animal science in order to produce or refine agricultural products. Course topics typically include but are not limited to microbiology, genetics, growth and reproduction, structural basis of function in living systems, chemistry of living systems, quantitative problem-solving, and data acquisition and display. These courses also often cover the ethics of biotechnology.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:04', '2020-06-09 09:45:04'),
(1481, 'import', 'AZ18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '309', 'Particular Topics in Agricultural Production/Processing', 'These courses examine specific topics related to producing and processing agricultural products (such as meat cutting) rather than provide a general study of production or processing.', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', '0', '40664', NULL, '1', '18309', '18', 'Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources', '309', 'Particular Topics in Agricultural Production/Processing', 'These courses examine specific topics related to producing and processing agricultural products (such as meat cutting) rather than provide a general study of production or processing.', '0', '0', '0', '1', NULL, 1, 1, '2020-06-09 09:45:04', '2020-06-09 09:45:04'),
